releases.name: release build: v04.06.00
releases.description:
<details>
  <summary>bug fix: uncaught exception when CastSession ends in "CAST_ONLY" mode</summary>

  ```text  
  -------------------------------------------------------------------
  
  issue:
    * uncaught exception leads to crash
  
  steps to reproduce:
    * pause "VideoActivity"
    * click "stop" on TV remote control to end CastSession
  
  -------------------------------------------------------------------
  
  CastPlayer:
  ===========
  
  onSessionEnded()
   -> setRemoteMediaClient(null)
      -> sessionAvailabilityListener.onCastSessionUnavailable()
  
  VideoManager:
  =============
  
  onCastSessionUnavailable()
   -> release(false)
      -> release_castPlayer(false)
         -> castPlayer.release()
  
  CastPlayer:
  ===========
  
  release()
   -> sessionManager.endCurrentSession(false)
      -> ERROR: because this entire chain of events started when the current session ended..
  
  solution:
  =========
  
  in: VideoManager
  in: -> onCastSessionUnavailable
  old:   -> release(false)
  new:   -> release(true)  // retain_cast_session
  
  -------------------------------------------------------------------
  
  old:
  ====
  
    @Override
    public void onCastSessionUnavailable() {
      if (castPlayer == null) return;
  
      if (playbackMode == PlaybackMode.CAST_ONLY) {
        setPlaybackMode(PlaybackMode.RELEASED);
      }
      else {
        setCurrentPlayer(exoPlayer);
      }
    }
  
  new:
  ====
  
    @Override
    public void onCastSessionUnavailable() {
      if (castPlayer == null) return;
  
      if (playbackMode == PlaybackMode.CAST_ONLY) {
        setPlaybackMode(PlaybackMode.RELEASED_ALL_BUT_CAST_SESSION);
      }
      else {
        setCurrentPlayer(exoPlayer);
      }
    }
  
  -------------------------------------------------------------------
  ```
</details>

releases.name: release build: v04.04.00
releases.description:
<details>
  <summary>bug fix: add "RELEASED_ALL_BUT_CAST_SESSION" mode</summary>
  
  ## issue this solves:
  
  * in "BrowserActivity":
    * select video URL(s) to watch
  * in "VideoActivity":
    * start a cast session
    * playlist of video URLs appears on screen
    * when a video in playlist is clicked:
      * video queue loads in Chromecast
      * position in queue skips to selected playlist item
    * "onPause" runs when Activity screen is closed
      * "PlayerManager" enters "CAST_ONLY" mode and releases all other resources
  * in "BrowserActivity":
    * select video URL(s) to watch
  * in "VideoActivity":
    * "onResume" runs and detects that "PlayerManager" is running in "CAST_ONLY" mode
      * previously:
        * "PlayerManager" transitioned: "CAST_ONLY" -> "RELEASED" -> "NORMAL"
        * "RELEASED" mode releases all resources, including closing the CastSession
        * "currentPlayer" is an instance of ExoPlayer
      * now:
        * "PlayerManager" transitions: "CAST_ONLY" -> "RELEASED_ALL_BUT_CAST_SESSION" -> "NORMAL"
        * "RELEASED_ALL_BUT_CAST_SESSION" mode is identical to "RELEASED", but CastSession is not closed
        * "currentPlayer" is an instance of CastPlayer
          * the previous video queue that was casting continues uninterupted
          * the new playlist of video URLs appears on screen
          * when a video in playlist is clicked:
            * new video queue loads in Chromecast
            * position in new queue skips to selected playlist item
</details>

releases.description:
update ExoPlayer libraries …

in response to [issue #2](https://github.com/warren-bank/Android-RTSP-IPCam-Viewer/issues/2) the branch ['dev/c516740'](https://github.com/warren-bank/Android-RTSP-IPCam-Viewer/tree/dev/c516740) was added to update ExoPlayer from: ['dev-v2-rtsp'](https://github.com/tresvecesseis/ExoPlayer/tree/dev-v2-rtsp) which is currently at commit: [c516740](https://github.com/tresvecesseis/ExoPlayer/tree/c516740526818d6275188a73b5fdcab9a2a74821) __problems:__ - the [core library](https://github.com/tresvecesseis/ExoPlayer/commits/dev-v2-rtsp/library/core) has been changed _A LOT_ recently * this reflects its recent [rapid development](https://github.com/google/ExoPlayer/commits/release-v2/library/core) in the [official repo](https://github.com/google/ExoPlayer/tree/release-v2), which is currently at commit: [6aa35aa](https://github.com/google/ExoPlayer/tree/6aa35aaaa5f594dfec8e9916d962676f671424f5) * `tresvecesseis` repo is behind.. though they make a good effort to merge changes pretty often - the rtsp (and related) library has fallen out of step with the core * there are a lot of breaking changes __alpha:__ - the core library in `tresvecesseis` repo could not be used as-is * contains broken code * I generated a patch file and updated only the core library to match the current state of the official repo - some aspects of this patch needed to be held back * eventually, the rtsp (and related) library will need to be modified to work with the official core library * for the moment, a few minor artifacts that were removed are still present - there was one fairly major change to the core library that I didn't feel would be right to try to roll back, so instead I modified the rtsp (and related) library.. slightly - for more details, see: [notes.txt](https://github.com/warren-bank/Android-RTSP-IPCam-Viewer/blob/v02.01.00-alpha.01/.etc/exoplayer_updates/c516740_6aa35aa/1-v02.01.00-alpha.01/1.%20notes.txt) __result:__ - everything seems to work as expected - not sure if there is any improvement over the current stable release: [v02.00.00](https://github.com/warren-bank/Android-RTSP-IPCam-Viewer/releases/tag/v02.00.00)

releases.name: json/v1.04
releases.description:
[v1.04] housekeeping

previously:
- the addon that fully supports user-defined javascript
  (and is evaluated using `eval()`)
  was isolated to the repo `moz-rewrite`
- the addon that only supports user-defined JSON
  was isolated to the repo `moz-rewrite-amo`

now:
- the addon that fully supports user-defined javascript
  (and is evaluated using `eval()`)
  has been migrated to the branch `js/eval/master`
  of the repo `moz-rewrite`
- the addon that only supports user-defined JSON
  has been migrated to the branch `json/master`
  of the repo `moz-rewrite`.
  - the repo `moz-rewrite-amo` has been deprecated
- a new addon that fully supports user-defined javascript
  (and is evaluated using `Cu.evalInSandbox()`)
  has been added to the branch `js/Cu.evalInSandbox/master`
  of the repo `moz-rewrite`

see:
- tagged release `json/v1.04` attachment: `changelog.sh`
- this shell script summarizes the key points of this migration process

in terms of necessary housekeeping for `json/master`:
- the following needed adjustment:
  - namespacing-
    - name of the addon (to differentiate it from other variations)
    - name of preferences branch
    - name of resource/content URLs
    - contract id of component
    - placeholder/suggested file paths to input files
  - filenames
  - URLs in copyright comment blocks

releases.description:
[v2.02] adds an "interactive download mode" option to the "saved requests" replay dialog window

there are two new checkbox fields:
1. interactively identify each partial/incomplete download file
   
   when checked:
   - each "saved request" that is selected for replay
     will trigger a file picker dialog,
     which allows the user to select the file path
     to a file that is the result of a partial/incomplete download.
   
   when unchecked:
   - each saved request that is selected for replay
     will begin being saved to the "default download directory",
     as selected in the addon preferences.
2. fallback behavior when "cancel" is chosen in interactive dialog
   
   when checked:
   - proceed with download and save to default directory
   
   when unchecked:
   - skip replay of the specific saved request

releases.name: js/eval/v2.01
js/eval/v2.00
releases.description:
[v2.00] adds the ability to:
- `save()` requests from within javascript functions, which can occur in either the _request_ or _response_ data sets
- view a list of all saved requests within a dialog window that can be opened from the "tools" menu
- select any number of these saved requests and select a download utility (requires configuration in preferences) to "replay" these requests.

example:

``` javascript
[
{
    "url": /^.*$/,
    "headers": function(){
        if (response.content_length > 20000000){
            save();
        }
        return {};
    }
}
]
```

when the download utility is invoked, it's passed command-line configuration arguments that push all of the original request's HTTP headers, as well as POST data (if there was any).

additional command-line options are configurable in preferences. I chose sane defaults.. mainly focused on the use-case for resuming interrupted downloads.. but it's all right there.. so a user can tweak the settings as needed.

in this commit, 'wget' is currently the only supported download utility.

immediately after this tagged release, there's going to be a branch named 'replay/curl' added.
I've already written an implementation to support 'curl', however there's a bit of a snag.. that I'll discuss in greater detail when that commit is made; the issue has to do with how 'curl' uses the `current working directory`.. and our inability to assign it.

sufficed to say, adding additional download tools is pretty straight forward.. and the commit that adds 'curl' will serve as a roadmap for exactly where all the touch-points are.

as for 'curl' itself.. and bringing that utility into `master`.. the concept of using a default download directory is going to need to be revisited/reworked. If the main use-case is resuming broken downloads.. then it would be a nice feature to offer the user the option (when selecting which saved requests to replay) whether or not (for each download) to interactively locate an existing file on the file system.. that the download utility will append additional data onto. This way, tools (like 'wget') that can use a default download directory will give the user the option to either:
- "replay" several saved requests in bulk, and silently (re)download the files to a single predefined directory without requiring any user interaction, _or_
- be prompted (for each download) to identify the filepath where the original/partial file lives

..which is awesome functionality!
Additionally, it would allow using 'curl'.. if only in this "interactive" mode.

I should probably say a lot more about this release.. it's a huge step forward..

I'll most likely add to this description tomorrow. For right now, I want to push the 'curl' branch (and get a little rest).
